TO: PYKE JOHNSON, Jr.

CC, 1 p.





Brockway Hotel

Brockway, California

August 16, 1959

Dear Mr. Johnson,

I have decided to postpone indefinitely the writing of PALE FIRE.1 The work has not been advancing and I have come to the conclusion that the very existence of the contractual obligation has been interfering with the free development of the novel. I am not sure I shall ever write it; but if I do it will 